e="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Music/AKB48">AKG49</a>.<ul><li> Also the giant squid from the same episode looks a lot like a <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Franchise/SuperMarioBros" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Franchise/SuperMarioBros">Blooper</a>.</li></ul></li><li> The OVA is full of it, including Sheryl making remark how the room is lonely without Kokoro, which is a parody of the <img src="/images/article-hreficon-trivia.png" class="trivia1 rounded" title="This example contains a TRIVIA entry. It should be moved to the TRIVIA tab."><a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/UnCanceled" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/UnCanceled">(not-)ending</a> of <em><a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Anime/Doraemon" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Anime/Doraemon">Doraemon</a></em>. Of course, the room is cramped with other characters and isn't anywhere close to lonely.</li><li> In the <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/Eyecatch" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/Eyecatch">Eyecatch</a> of episode two of Season Two, Saki looks like a certain <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Manga/SquidGirl" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Manga/SquidGirl">invader from the sea</a>.<ul><li> In the same episode the diplomat, after his truck is lifted in the air. Says <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Film/ETTheExtraterrestrial" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Film/ETTheExtraterrestrial">Diplomat Phone Home</a>.</li><li> At the end when The Phantom Thief Empire are thrown back in jail, right next door there are a bunch of pirates, which includes <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Franchise/PiratesOfTheCaribbean" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Franchise/PiratesOfTheCaribbean">Captain Jack Sparrow</a>, <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Series/KaizokuSentaiGokaiger" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Series/KaizokuSentaiGokaiger">Captain Marvelous</a>, an yellow octopus with a <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Manga/OnePiece" title="/pmwiki